[src:adams-run-south-carolina/2020-united-states-census] Louis Area Census Office was May 11, 2020.
[src:adams-run-south-carolina/2020-united-states-census] On May 21, 2020, procurement information for two contracts was entered into the Federal Procurement Data System.
[src:adams-run-south-carolina/2020-united-states-census] A press release on May 22, 2020, announced May 25 "restart" dates for ten more states.
[src:adams-run-south-carolina/2020-united-states-census] An OSHA complaint was made from Concord, California, on April 3, 2020, that there were at least two confirmed cases of COVID-19 unrecorded on OSHA 300 logs and that employees were working in close quarters with no disinfection of shared equipment such as headsets, laptops, and tablets.
[src:adams-run-south-carolina/2020-united-states-census] The published restart date for the Concord, California, Area Census Office was May 25, 2020.
